Health workers wearing PPE prepare to test a woman for COVID-19. AFP/Emmanuel Croset JOHANNESBURG - A total of 21,427 new COVID-19 infections have been reported in the last 24-hours. Gauteng accounts for just over 10,500 of them. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Stricter restrictions recommended The NICD said 411 COVID-19 related deaths have also been recorded. A total of 70,797 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours.